cs.DC, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with communication in distributed systems and proposes a formalization of it.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as Petri nets are a formalism used in logic and the paper presents a Petri net interpretation of the Integrated Model of Distributed Systems.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with modeling communication in distributed systems, which is relevant to programming languages that support distributed computing.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper presents a method of automatic process extraction in the Petri net interpretation of the Integrated Model of Distributed Systems, which is relevant to software engineering.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with modeling and analyzing distributed systems, which can be seen as a control problem.
